A Florida mother is furious at a police dispatcher who would not send officers to help when her baby son was trapped inside her sweltering car.

Shana Dees was running errands on Saturday with her 10-month-old son Jack. It was about noon when they left a CVS pharmacy in New Tampa and and Dees moved Jack from the shopping cart to his car seat.

The cart began to move away because of the parking lot's uneven ground. Dees ran over to secure the cart — but turned back to a frightening scene.

'Those three seconds, when I was moving the cart, he hit the lock button,' Dees told WFTS.

